WVSD: Dear Parents,

Starting on Wednesday March 25th Weldon Valley School will be delivering student lunches for those who wish to have one on Monday through Thursday. For lunches to be delivered the parent must call the school daily at 645-2411 between the hours of 7:30 AM to 9:00 AM to order. It is important that when you call to tell us how many student lunches are needed. Lunch prices will be the same as usual including those students that receive free/reduced lunch. Delivery time for the lunches will be around noon. Fort Morgan students who want lunch delivered will pick them up at the onion shed.

If you have questions please contact the school.

Thanks

post_text:
Dear Weldon Valley Parents and Elementary Students,

Teacher appreciation week is coming up, May 6-9, and we would like your help in showering our teachers with gifts of thanks. Each day will have a theme, you may participate in as many days as you would like, or feel free to do your own thing completely. Thank you for supporting our teachers and staff at Weldon Valley School, we are very fortunate to have such wonderful, hardworking, and caring teachers.

Sincerely,
Weldon Valley PTO

Monday, May 6th - Homemade Day: Something homemade just for your teacher. Ex. Picture, cars, cookies, muffins.

Tuesday, May 7th - Blue and Gold Day: Something blue or gold to show your school spirit. Ex. Blue Pen, yellow daisies, lemonade.

Wednesday, May 8th - Sweets Day: Something sweet for your teacher. Ex. Chocolate, candy bar, DQ gift card.

Thursday, May 9th - Relaxation Day: Help your teacher wind down after a hard week. Ex. Nail polish, candles

If you would like to help us for a month (of your choice), please let us know! 9:30am - Weldon Valley vs. Briggsdale (on AM 1400 KFTM and kftm.net)

Please bring donations to the school office and we will get them taken care of.

Thank you so much in advance for all your help!

post_text: We had a wonderful time on the R.C. trip today. We had so much fun! Thank you to the kids that worked so hard to earn the trip, and the parents and staff that joined us on our trip. To the parents and teachers that made it posible for the kids to earn this trip a big thank you. Our wonderful bus drivers did a great job of getting us there and home safe, so a big thanks to you! Thanks to Gail Johnson for all her hard work putting R.C. together ! And a BIG thanks to all the kids. You were so well behaved. We were all very proud of you. We were told a number of times what good kids we have. We alway knew it, but it is always nice to have others recognise what wonderful kids we are lucky to have at this school. Hope you all had fun!
